HEADWORD: Guarana
<hw>Gua"ra*na`</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Pg.]</ety>
<fld>(Med.)</fld> <def>A preparation from the seeds of <spn>Paullinia
sorbilis</spn>, a woody climber of Brazil, used in making an astringent
drink, and also in the cure of headache.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

